      "versionNonce": 259648938,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1770398174014,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "LLD \n\nAmazon Locker\n\nInterface Locker{\nsize: enum;\n\nlocker_enum deposit(package, size);\nvoid pickup(locker_id, code);\nbool isLockerAvailable(size);\n\n// some utility functions \nisEmpty\ndecrease\nincrease\n\n\n}",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "LLD \n\nAmazon Locker\n\nInterface Locker{\nsize: enum;\n\nlocker_enum deposit(package, size);\nvoid pickup(locker_id, code);\nbool isLockerAvailable(size);\n\n// some utility functions \nisEmpty\ndecrease\nincrease\n\n\n}",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "z5p_G4T4GJW7Tkp9cZF6X",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -2362.8117612560063,
      "y": 1082.4524899034755,
      "width": 662.1680874090102,
      "height": 975,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0g",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 193192566,
      "version": 2248,
      "versionNonce": 799316470,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770398174014,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Tinder(10:20am)\n\nFR:\n1. User should be able to see profiles based on \ntheir preferences\n2. User should be able to left or right swipe \nfor yes/no\n3. Should get a notification if they got a right \nswipe over their right swipe\n4. Should create a profile with preferences and \nspecify a max distance.\n\nNFR:\n1. the system should have strong consistency on \nright swipes, if a user swipes yes on a user who has already swiped\nyes, the users should be matched without fail.\n2. showing the recommended profiles should be low consistency\n3. should be able to handle lots of daily users/concurrent users\n(20M daily actives, 100 swipes/user/day on avg)\n4. should avoid showing profiles on which the user has already\nswiped a no.\n\n\nCore Entities:\n1. User\n2. User's Recommendation Feed\n3. Matched Users\n4. Profiles\n5. Notifications\n\nAPIs:\n1. POST /profile {userdetails, preferences, distanceprefered} ->\nprofileId\n2. GET /recommendations -> profile[]\n3. POST /swipeLeft {profileid, timestamp} -> ack or void not sure\n4. POST /swipeRight {profileid, timestamp} -> ack or void not sure\n5. GET /matches -> matchedProfiles[]\n6. \n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Tinder(10:20am)\n\nFR:\n1. User should be able to see profiles based on \ntheir preferences\n2. User should be able to left or right swipe \nfor yes/no\n3. Should get a notification if they got a right \nswipe over their right swipe\n4. Should create a profile with preferences and \nspecify a max distance.\n\nNFR:\n1. the system should have strong consistency on \nright swipes, if a user swipes yes on a user who has already swiped\nyes, the users should be matched without fail.\n2. showing the recommended profiles should be low consistency\n3. should be able to handle lots of daily users/concurrent users\n(20M daily actives, 100 swipes/user/day on avg)\n4. should avoid showing profiles on which the user has already\nswiped a no.\n\n\nCore Entities:\n1. User\n2. User's Recommendation Feed\n3. Matched Users\n4. Profiles\n5. Notifications\n\nAPIs:\n1. POST /profile {userdetails, preferences, distanceprefered} -> profileId\n2. GET /recommendations -> profile[]\n3. POST /swipeLeft {profileid, timestamp} -> ack or void not sure\n4. POST /swipeRight {profileid, timestamp} -> ack or void not sure\n5. GET /matches -> matchedProfiles[]\n6. \n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
